      "arraySize": 1,
      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "authtype -  - The type of authentication.\n\n none - No authentication basic - Basic authentication is base-64 encoded username and password. digest - Digest authentication is base-64 encoded username and password that's encrypted with a hashing function. Digest is a more secure version of Basic authentication. ouath1 - Version 1 of OAuth. OAuth1 requires App Key, App Secret, User OAuth Token, and User OAuth Secret. These can be found via the account on the web server that request is being sent to. For example, in the case of the Twitter API the values of these 4 parameters can be found under the account profile. ouath2 - Version 2 of OAuth. OAuth2 first requires an HTTP request be sent to the web server to acquire the Client ID and token. It can be acquired using a browser.",
      "tooltip": "",
      "help": "",
      "units": "",
      "examples": [],
